      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they both have points but it feels kinda like a cop-out to say they're equal. if u had to pick one that actually aligns better with modern human rights standards, wouldn't the asylum argument be the \"correct\" moral choice? border security often feels like it's just used as an excuse for being exclusionary.",
