      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait so u basically saying border security is just a way to violate human rights? that seems like a pretty extreme way to frame it. what about the argument that a country can't actually protect its own citizens' rights or maintain its social safety net if it doesn't have control over who enters? isn't that a valid moral argument for a government too?",
